<HL>
   Chrysler Idles Assembly Plants
</HL>
<DATE>
04/02/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C9
</SO>
<CO>
   C
</CO>
<IN>
AUTOMOBILES (AUT)
</IN>
<LP>
   HIGHLAND PARK, Mich. -- Chrysler Corp. said it is
temporarily halting production at four production facilities
this week because of sluggish sales.
   The No. 3 auto maker is idling assembly plants in
Belvidere, Ill., Newark, Del., Toledo, Ohio, and Sterling
Heights, Mich. The facilities are scheduled to resume
production April 9. A total of about 12,700 workers will be
affected.
